\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\fs24 1. What is a protocol stack, and how is it used in web development?\fs32\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\fs24 Ans: \b0 A protocol stack is a set of communication protocols that are layered on top of each other to facilitate communication between different devices or applications. Each layer of the protocol stack provides a different set of services, and the layers work together to provide end-to-end communication.\par
In web development, the most commonly used protocol stack is the TCP/IP protocol stack. This protocol stack is used to facilitate communication between web servers and web clients, such as web browsers.\par
The TCP/IP protocol stack consists of several layers, each with a specific set of functions:\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b Application layer:\b0  This layer includes the protocols used for web communication, such as HTTP (Hypertext Transfer Protocol), FTP (File Transfer Protocol), SMTP (Simple Mail Transfer Protocol), and DNS (Domain Name System).\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Transport layer:\b0  This layer provides end-to-end data transfer between web servers and clients. The most commonly used protocol in this layer is TCP (Transmission Control Protocol), which ensures reliable and ordered data transmission.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Internet layer:\b0  This layer is responsible for routing data between different networks. The protocol used in this layer is the Internet Protocol (IP).\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Network Access layer:\b0  This layer provides the physical connection between devices and networks, such as Ethernet or Wi-Fi.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj In web development, developers need to understand the different layers of the TCP/IP protocol stack to ensure that their web applications can communicate with web servers and clients effectively. For example, they need to understand how to use HTTP to transfer data between web browsers and web servers, and they need to understand how to use TCP to ensure reliable data transfer.\par
